    "preview_source": "tier7-ingest-v0.2",
    "summary": "Animal power remains crucial for transportation, agricultural activities, and rural trade in low- and middle-income countries. In Ethiopia, donkeys are essential for both farming and non-farming households, providing transport and draught power, contributing significantly to livelihoods. Despite their importance, donkeys have received limited research attention. The lack of empirical evidence on the economic contribution of donkeys has led to their undervaluation and exclusion from policy with chronic underinvestment, and poor welfare outcomes. This study aimed to investigate the socioeconomic contributions of donkeys and the impact of disease and injury on household livelihoods and the national economy in Ethiopia. Data were collected through household surveys, focus group discussions, ke"
